I love refried beans. I've been eating and enjoying them for almost four decades. However ... these aren't them! It would be much closer to what is in the can to call them bean paste -pale and flavorless, at that. I've eaten probably 20 different brands of refried beans over the years. Though some are better than others, they all share something this product doesn't have: whole or parts of pinto beans. Plus a certain darkness of color suggests that they are indeed pinto beans and are refried. This product is a very pale paste.<br />Refried Pinto Beans ... Not
